OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSitcom writer and producer 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FNorman Lear dies at 101    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Sitcom writer and producer Norman Lear 
OL,6, has died of natural causes at his home 
OL,7, in Los Angeles aged 101, a spokesperson
OL,8, for his family has confirmed.          
OL,10,FLear was best known for his            
OL,11,Ftrailblazing sitcoms in the 1970s and  
OL,12,F80s, including Sanford and Son and The 
OL,13,FJeffersons.                            
OL,15,FThe celebrated US writer was a         
OL,16,Ffive-time Emmy Award winner and a      
OL,17,Fmember of the Television Academy Hall  
OL,18,Fof Fame.                               
OL,20,FIn a statement his family said knowing 
OL,21,FLear had "been the greatest of gifts". 
